url.video:title: Signs of Health - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Have you ever wondered if your cat is as healthy on the inside as on the outside? The best way to monitor your cat's health is by paying attention to their behavior. Signs of a healthy cat include clear eyes, shiny coat and a normal activity level.
Put this knowledge to work. Try our Signs of Health activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/health-socialization/signs-of-health

url.video:title: Safe Outdoor Experiences - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Have you ever noticed your cat staring out the window in the sunlight? Learning how to provide safe cat outdoor experiences is just one of the ways we can provide the right stimulation to live their true nature.
Master the skill of Leash Walking your cat with our Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/exercise-play/leash-walking

url.video:title: Healthy Hydration - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Have you ever noticed your cat drinking water from a faucet or something other than her water bowl? Experts believe that cats like to obtain fluids from multiple sources. Learning about how to keep your cat hydrated is just one way we can better understand our cat's true nature.
Need more guidance? Try our Healthy Hydration Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/feeding-hydration/healthy-hydration

url.video:title: Meet Our Veterinarian - Deb - Purina ONE® True Nature of Cats
url.video:description:
Meet Deb, the resident veterinarian of the Purina ONE® cat expert team. Deb understands the needs of cats, especially when it comes to health and nutrition. She stresses the importance of getting an annual health exam for your cat to help identify any signs of disease or illness. Deb believes she has made a difference in the lives of cats and wants to help you discover the true nature of your cat so it can live the best life possible.
Learn more in our Yearly Checkup Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/health-socialization/yearly-checkup

url.video:title: Meet Our Nutritionist - Fred - Purina ONE® True Nature of Cats
url.video:description:
Meet Fred, our cat nutritionist and member of the Purina ONE® cat expert team. Fred loves working with Purina because of his love for animals and knowing that his research helps cats live healthy lives. For example, he knows that cat hydration is very important however some cats do not like drinking from a bowl, so he proposes alternative ways to offer water, e.g. dripping or running. Further, he suggests that a combination of dry and wet cat food may help prevent dehydration.
Want tips for introducing wet food to your cat's diet? Try our Wet + Dry Food activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/feeding-hydration/wet-plus-dry-together

url.video:title: The Importance of Play - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Sandra, our nutritional behaviorist, explains how stalking and pouncing are instinctual cat behaviors that can be positively fostered with play. Learning about purposeful cat play is just one way we can better understand our cat's true nature.
Playtime enriches the feeding experience for your cat. Learn how in our Playing Together Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/exercise-play/playing-together

url.video:title: Discover the Benefits of Play for Your Cat with Purina ONE®
url.video:description:
We asked members of our True Nature of Cats by Purina ONE Facebook community to share videos of their cats at play. We put them together in this short video to serve as examples of healthy play and explain the benefits of play, including exercise, mental stimulus, building trust between you and your cat, and stress relief.
Master a number of techniques for helping your cat burn off energy and calories between meals. Try our Playing Together activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/exercise-play/playing-together

url.video:title: Natural Athletes - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Cats are naturally agile and athletic at home and in the wild. Their bodies are built to jump and stretch with flexibility, and crouch and crawl with ease. Sandra from the Purina ONE expert cat team gives quick tips to help your cat get active and let her true agility and athletic ability shine through.
Cats seek perches that are up off the ground. Learn how getting up and down lets your cat show off her graceful agility in our Vertical Spaces Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/behavior-environment/vertical-spaces

url.video:title: Interpreting Tails - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Sandra, our nutritional behaviorist, explains the nuances of cat tail language and the meanings behind different positions to help you understand how your cat is feeling and what she is trying to communicate. Learning about cat tail body language is just one way we can better understand our cat's true nature.
Ready to learn how to decode more of your cat's way of communicating? Try our Interpreting Body Language activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/health-socialization/body-language

url.video:title: Understanding Cat Behavior - Purina ONE® True Nature of Cats
url.video:description:
There are many preconceived notions about cats, like they aren't social or can't be trained. Purina ONE cat expert and veterinarian Deb explains cat behavior and how it is possible to train cats using the clicker method. Cats are built for activity and clicker training can provide them with mental stimulation. Understanding cat behavior and cat needs can help you better understand the true nature of your cat.
Gain a deeper understanding of your cat's behavior. Explore our activities in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities

url.video:title: Meet Our Cat Behaviorist - Sandra - Purina ONE® True Nature of Cats
url.video:description:
Sandra is the resident Nutritional Behaviorist on the Purina ONE® cat expert team. Her role is to conduct research to advance the knowledge of the feeding behavior of cats. Purina ONE® believes that stimulation can make feeding time more pleasurable for cats through cat food taste, smell, texture and size. Sandra loves what she does and knows that her research will truly benefit the lives of cats.
A good feeding experience for your cat starts with a proper dish. Learn why in our Feeding Dish vs. Bowl activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/feeding-hydration/feeding-dish-vs-bowl

url.video:title: Curious by Nature - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Jill, our behaviorist, explains why cats are curious by nature and like to climb up to high perches. Understanding that cats like to safely survey their environment from above is just one way we can better understand our cat's true nature.
Learn some easy ways you can give your cat access to the high perches she craves in our Vertical Spaces Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/behavior-environment/vertical-spaces

url.video:title: Adjusting to Change - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Jill, our behaviorist, shares tips on how to help your cat adapt to changes in their environment. Learning the steps to help your cat adapt to change is respectful to how they are and who they were born to be.
Want to gain a deeper understanding of your cat's behavior? Explore our activities in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities

url.video:title: Stimulating Sounds - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Have you ever noticed how cats respond to certain sounds around the house? Her ears perk up and her whiskers twitch when she hears things like trickling water or birds chirping. Your cat is acting on instincts similar to those observed in the African Wildcat in her natural habitat. You can nurture your cat's instincts by offering stimulating sounds in your home so she can live her true nature.
Learn more about why it's good to give your cat access to the sounds, sights and smells of nature. Try our Rooms with a View Activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/behavior-environment/rooms-with-a-view

url.video:title: Harmonious Multi-Cat Households - Purina ONE® Video Series "Enriching the Lives of Cats"
url.video:description:
Sandra, our nutritional behaviorist, shares tips on how to create a harmonious multi-cat household. Learn to let your cats live their true nature, the way they were born to be.
Want to understand more about your cat's true nature? Learn about this and more in our Litter Box Acumen activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/health-socialization/litter-box-acumen

url.video:title: Cat Behaviorist - Jill - Purina ONE® True Nature of Cats
url.video:description:
Jill is a cat behaviorist and part of the Purina ONE cat expert team. Intrigued by the subtleties of cat behavior and communication, Jill aims to share her knowledge to help cat owners form a better bond with their cats.
Want to learn how to decode more of your cat's way of communicating? Try the Interpreting Body Language activity in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities/health-socialization/body-language

url.video:title: Meet Our Cat Health and Behavior Experts Purina ONE True Nature
url.video:description:
Discover your cat's true nature with our team of cat health and behavior experts. Our cat team has spent so much time working to understand cat behavior and nutrition to help better the lives of cats everywhere. Fred, our Cat Nutritionist has over 17 years of experience at Purina and understands feline physiology and nutrition. Deb is our Veterinarian and is an encyclopedia of cat insights. Sandra is our Cat Behaviorist with a background in psychology and nutrition.
Want to understand more about your cat's true nature? Explore our activities in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities

url.video:title: Who Is Your Cat Born To Be? - Cash Episode 1 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
Join Purina ONE on a journey to discover the true nature of cats with Cash, a kitten from the North Shore Animal League America. Over the next few months, we will follow Cash as he finds a permanent, loving home and is raised the way his true nature intended. Cash shares his roots and behavioral instincts with the African Wildcat. Even though he is a domestic cat, he was born to run, jump, scratch, climb and pounce just like his ancestors.
Dig deep into your cat's behavior with the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/TrueNatureJournal

url.video:title: Discovering Cat Physiology - Cash Episode 2 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description: What makes Cash so similar to his ancestor, the African Wildcat? It all starts with physiology. Legs for jumping, claws for climbing and eyes to see in the brightest day or darkest night. Understanding similarities in physiology between the African Wildcat and the domestic cat helps us to better appreciate what domestic cats were born to be. Get expert tips and techniques for understanding your cat in the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/TrueNatureJournal

url.video:title: Understanding Cat Behavior - Cash Episode 3 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
They're born to be cats. Instinctual hunting behaviors have been carried over from their ancestors and are demonstrated in domestic cats mostly during playtime. They love to run, leap, stalk and pounce. All these behaviors are completely natural and should be fostered in order to raise a healthy and happy cat. Toys can help them stay active and redirect their energy to a positive place.
Dig deep into your cat's behavior with the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/TrueNatureJournal

url.video:title: Cat Stress: Good and Bad - Cash Episode 4 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
Join Cash as he leaves the shelter for his new home with Ashlee. New environments mean lots of new things for cats to discover; new sounds, smells, and spaces. Too much at once can be overwhelming. But if introduced properly, new experiences can be exciting.
Help her feel more comfortable with the True Nature Journal Hideouts activity: http://www.purinaone.com/HideoutsJournal

url.video:title: True Nature of Cats' Health - Cash Episode 5 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
Today Cash is headed to his first visit with his new veterinarian, Dr. Manning. He will check for signs of health in Cash such as clear eyes and nose, a shiny coat, and a healthy weight. Like the African Wildcat, Cash lives a healthy lifestyle with mental stimulation, proper diet and exercise, however it is still very important to visit the veterinarian regularly to maintain good health.
Keep your cat in good health with the Yearly Checkup activity in the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/CheckupJournal

url.video:title: Born to Hunt - Cash Episode 6 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
Hunting behaviors are instinctual in cats, domestic or wild. We can observe these behaviors in Cash during play when he chases, stalks and pounces - just like his ancestor. Purposeful play which imitates hunting behaviors in cats is important to keep cats active and expense energy. Join our community to learn more about cat toys that can help your cat stay active and simulate the hunt the way your cat's true nature intended.
Mimic the hunt for food with the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/PuzzleFeederJournal

url.video:title: Feeding Your Cat's True Nature - Cash Episode 7 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
For Cash, mealtime is more than just eating -- it is an experience. The feeding experience is enriching for him when he can taste and chew different flavors and textures. Combining dry and wet cat food in his diet mirrors the experience his ancestor, the African Wildcat, has in the wild. Feeding toys like exercise feeders or puzzle feeders help encourage this activity helping him to be the cat he was born to be.
Mimic the hunt for food with the Puzzle Feeder activity in the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/PuzzleFeederJournal

url.video:title: The Social Nature of Cats - Cash Episode 8 - Purina ONE® True Nature
url.video:description:
Properly socializing domestic cats is important so that they can form strong social bonds for a happy, healthy life. In the wild, the African Wildcat lives a solitary life because food is too widely dispersed. Without the competition, Cash can have human friends and play with other cats to develop strong social skills. Learn tips for introducing cats to other animals, so everything can be fun and games.
Enrich your cat's experience with the True Nature Journal: http://www.purinaone.com/TrueNatureJournal

url.video:title: Healthy Metabolism Cat Food Commercial - Play Eat Rest - Purina ONE®
url.video:description:
Cats were born to play, eat and rest. Purina ONE® created Healthy Metabolism wet and dry cat food to fuel the metabolic cycle cats were born to have. Learn more at http://www.purinaone.com/healthymetabolism and http://www.purinaone.com/truenature
Want to understand more about your cat's true nature? Explore our activities in the True Nature Journal by Purina ONE: http://www.purinaone.com/cat-journal/activities
